Reproducibility of GIScience MSc Theses - Self-assessment experiment

Carlos Granell

Universitat Juame I of Castellón, Spain

15/04/2020 (updated 02 septiembre, 2020)

Abstract

This document analyses the responses to a pre-questionnaire and post-questionnaire in the framework of the [experiment on the self-assesment of reproducibility levels of master’s thesis in GIS science] (https://osf.io/j97zp/) carried out during the academic year 2019/20 with master’s students enrolled in two GIS-related master’s programs: Erasmus Master MSc in Geospatial Technologies and MSc Geomatics.

1 Preliminaries

1.1 Software dependencies

This document does not install the required R packages by default. You can run the script install.R to install all required dependencies on a new R installation, or use install.packages(..) to install missing R packages.

1.2 Required libraries

library("tidyverse")

To create the PDF of the computational notebook you can run the following commands in a new R session. If you have problems rendering the PDF you can execute each chunk independently in RStudio.

require("knitr")

2 Data

Students who have not participated in the self-assessment experiment (e.g., students who also answered the questionnaires as participants in a doctoral course at UJI), and the fields that refer to personal information (email, thesis handlers,and url to pdf files) are removed and therefore not used in the analysis.

3 Analysis

The following plots are based on the files C:/MyCode/self-assessment-experiment/data/pretest_filtered.csv and C:/MyCode/self-assessment-experiment/data-raw/selfassessment.csv. Only students from MSc in Geospatial Technologies (UJI, NOVA IMS, IFGI-WWU) and MSc Geomatics (TU Delft) are analysed.

3.1 Pre-test assessment

3.1.1 MSc in Geospatial Technologies (UJI, NOVA IMS, IFGI-WWU)

  • 54.16667% (13/24) of students (EM Master Geotech) provided a self-assessment statement. Two of them did not answered the pre-questionnaire, so they are not included in the analysis.

  • 12 students answered the pre-questionnaire. All but one added the self-assessment statement to their thesis manuscript.

  • 2 (out of 12) students have been previously trained on reproducible research practices.

3.1.1.1 Section 2: Current working practices

Note that responses to ‘working practices’ were multi-choice (N=12).
Practice group - Survey question
analysis What tools do you plan to use to ANALYSE data?
visualisation What tools do you plan to use to VISUALISE/PLOT data?
writing What tools do you plan to WRITE UP your master thesis or conference/journal article?
workflow What is your (expected) process of GETTING the summary data, statistical results, figures, maps and tables IN your master thesis document (or conference/journal article)?
